ğŸ Python3 â€“ Useful Codes & what they do

- print() â†’ displays output to the terminal.
- input() â†’ lets the user type something in and stores it.
- import â†’ pulls in external libraries (like time, os, gpiod).
- time.sleep(x) â†’ pauses program for x seconds.
- if / else â†’ decision-making (run different ode depending on conditions).
- for loop â†’ repeats code a set number of times.
- while loop â†’ repeats code until a condition is false (or forever if True).
- def function(): â†’ reusable block of code.
- class â†’ blueprint for creating objects with data + functions.
- try / except â†’ error handling (prevents crashes).
- with open("file") as f: â†’ open files safely (for reading/writing).
- pip install package (run in terminal) â†’ downloads and installs external Python libraries.
- venv (virtual environment) â†’ isolates project dependencies.
- __main__ check (if __name__ == "__main__":) â†’ makes scripts runnable directly.

ğŸ—ï¸ Core Concepts

- print() â†’ outputs text/data to the console.
- input() â†’ asks user for input and returns it as a string.
- type() â†’ tells you the data type of a value (int, str, list, etc.).
- len() â†’ returns length of a sequence (string, list, etc.).
- id() â†’ gives the memory reference (useful for debugging).

ğŸ”„ Control Flow

- if / elif / else â†’ branching logic (choose actions based on conditions).
- for loop â†’ repeats over a sequence (list, string, range).
- while loop â†’ repeats as long as a condition is True.
- break â†’ exits a loop early.
- continue â†’ skips the rest of the loop iteration and moves on.

ğŸ› ï¸ Functions & Scope
- def â†’ defines a reusable function.
- return â†’ sends a value back from a function.
- lambda â†’ quick, one-line anonymous functions.
- global / nonlocal â†’ lets functions modify variables outside their own scope.

â³ Time & Date

- time.sleep(x) â†’ pause program for x seconds.
- time.time() â†’ current timestamp (seconds since 1970).
- datetime.now() â†’ current date and time.
- strftime() â†’ formats date/time as text.

